#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.39:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.39:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga"
msgstr "4. Deities"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 39. Nidānasutta → kammanidānasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an6.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Nidānasutta"
msgstr "39. Sources"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.339"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.39:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, nidānāni kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these three sources that give rise to deeds."

msgctxt "an6.39:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an6.39:1.3"
msgid ""
"Lobho nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya, doso nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya, moho "
"nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr "Greed, hate, and delusion are sources that give rise to deeds."

msgctxt "an6.39:1.4"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, lobhā alobho samudeti;"
msgstr "Greed doesn’t give rise to contentment."

msgctxt "an6.39:1.5"
msgid "atha kho, bhikkhave, lobhā lobhova samudeti."
msgstr "Rather, greed just gives rise to greed."

# Note that this comes close to directly contradicting AN 4.193. Presumably the use of pema there implies something less pure than adosa or metta.
msgctxt "an6.39:1.6"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, dosā adoso samudeti;"
msgstr "Hate doesn’t give rise to love."

msgctxt "an6.39:1.7"
msgid "atha kho, bhikkhave, dosā dosova samudeti."
msgstr "Rather, hate just gives rise to hate."

msgctxt "an6.39:1.8"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, mohā amoho samudeti;"
msgstr "Delusion doesn’t give rise to understanding."

msgctxt "an6.39:1.9"
msgid "atha kho, bhikkhave, mohā mohova samudeti."
msgstr "Rather, delusion just gives rise to delusion."

# Interesting to see this precursor of the Abhidhammic “ye vā pan’aññe” here.
msgctxt "an6.39:1.10"
msgid ""
"Na, bhikkhave, lobhajena kammena dosajena kammena mohajena kammena devā "
"paññāyanti, manussā paññāyanti, yā vā panaññāpi kāci sugatiyo."
msgstr ""
"It’s not because of deeds born of greed, hate, and delusion that gods, "
"humans, or those in any other good places are found."

msgctxt "an6.39:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, lobhajena kammena dosajena kammena mohajena kammena "
"nirayo paññāyati tiracchānayoni paññāyati pettivisayo paññāyati, yā vā "
"panaññāpi kāci duggatiyo."
msgstr ""
"Rather, it’s because of deeds born of greed, hate, and delusion that hell, "
"the animal realm, the ghost realm, or any other bad places are found."

msgctxt "an6.39:1.12"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi nidānāni kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr "These are three sources that give rise to deeds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.39:2.1"
msgid "Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, nidānāni kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr "Mendicants, there are these three sources that give rise to deeds."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an6.39:2.3"
msgid ""
"Alobho nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya, adoso nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya, amoho "
"nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr ""
"Contentment, love, and understanding are sources that give rise to deeds."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.4"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, alobhā lobho samudeti;"
msgstr "Contentment doesn’t give rise to greed."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.5"
msgid "atha kho, bhikkhave, alobhā alobhova samudeti."
msgstr "Rather, contentment just gives rise to contentment."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.6"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, adosā doso samudeti;"
msgstr "Love doesn’t give rise to hate."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.7"
msgid "atha kho, bhikkhave, adosā adosova samudeti."
msgstr "Rather, love just gives rise to love."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.8"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, amohā moho samudeti;"
msgstr "Understanding doesn’t give rise to delusion."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.9"
msgid "atha kho, bhikkhave, amohā amohova samudeti."
msgstr "Rather, understanding just gives rise to understanding."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.10"
msgid ""
"Na, bhikkhave, alobhajena kammena adosajena kammena amohajena kammena nirayo "
"paññāyati tiracchānayoni paññāyati pettivisayo paññāyati, yā vā panaññāpi "
"kāci duggatiyo."
msgstr ""
"It’s not because of deeds born of contentment, love, and understanding that "
"hell, the animal realm, the ghost realm, or any other bad places are found."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, alobhajena kammena adosajena kammena amohajena kammena "
"devā paññāyanti, manussā paññāyanti, yā vā panaññāpi kāci sugatiyo."
msgstr ""
"Rather, it’s because of deeds born of contentment, love, and understanding "
"that gods, humans, or those in any other good places are found."

msgctxt "an6.39:2.12"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi nidānāni kammānaṃ samudayāyā”ti."
msgstr "These are three sources that give rise to deeds.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.39:2.13"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
